					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:38:34.806478-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:43:34.077737-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "QRiKqluJTLiOzMKQewMiHA=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "A user story, on the other hand, is a description of the user's work. It is literally the user's story. \n\nThe story describes a domain-level problem and, when fleshed out, describes how a user solves that problem when working at the domain level. \n\nThe story describes the user's work, not ours. \n\nA story does not describe or specify a computer program at all. It does not describe how a computer program works. Stories live in the domain—in the **problem space**.  \n\n(From Robert Martin, \"Clean Architecture\""
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:42:37.029053-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:42:37.029053-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "xVVSy3EqTWSr0yK77piKuw=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "A story is a *story*, not some broad \"I wish\" in a canned format. It describes actual (or at least desired) experience."
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T11:01:50.474472-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T11:02:34.077019-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "cUA+B/JZSEilwhEYluo7TA=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : " A **story \"card\"** holds anything from a single word to a sentence or two—enough to remind you what to talk about with a customer. \n \n \"Cook easily\" is way too broad, and means nothing. Everyone on the planet defines \"easy\" differently. Nobody would build a house without a kitchen. \n \n Here's a story: \"I make coffee using a prosumer espresso machine every morning. It's annoying that the machine is too far from the sink and that I can't plug anything else in while it's running.\" \n \n Here's another \"Every time I fry food, I set off the smoke detector.\" A story is a *story*, not some broad \"I wish\" in a canned format. It describes actual (or at least desired) experience."
						}
					]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:42:47.116094-04:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:42:47.116094-04:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "9rO1VeAkQPuaZnFml3jySQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "**Usser Story**"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:37:33.891651-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-05-02T10:43:56.866626-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "qyLPuJzlTE+sjGba2Qum0A=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "A use case is a description of the way that an automated system is used. \n\nIt specifies the input to be provided by the user, the output to be returned to the user, and the processing steps involved in producing that output.\" \n\nPut another way, a use case describes how a user uses a computer program. \n\nA use case describes how to use an existing program, or, if the program can't do everything necessary, it identifies aspects of the program we'll have to create. \n\nUse cases live in the **implementation space**.\n\n(From Robert Martin, \"Clean Architecture\""
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
